[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has a normal 1\S opening bid, 14 points and five trumps.

WEST has good 4-card support and 7 points, so she raises to 2\S, 
passed by EAST. 

WEST does not consider showing the \Hs, 
first because she knows there is a \S fit, and second because she doesn't have 
the 11 points needed to bid a new suit at the 2-level.}

